content: Minimalist Pomodoro app. Super cute. Exactly what I need.

What a cute little app, my productivity for doing uni work has definitely improved since using this. I really like all the options available as well; you can set the time allotted for work/break time, how many "sets" of work you do as well and white noise option is great. Like others have said, having a stats page so you could record your progress would make this app complete and grant it 5 star.
Really effective. Thank you, thank you, thank you. ‚úåÔ∏è
I refunded it right away because I couldn't do anything with settings.

a very simple pomodoro app that works fine but it would be better if it can give stats on how many hours in total that i was productive and the time of each pomodoro session (like 9:00-9:25 for example)
I like it, it's simple to use and fun. I got it yesterday but now the timer doesn't start when I flip it? Anyone know how to fix this...?

Ive had this app for my Android for three days and now the timer doesnt work. Ive restarted my phone. Ive done all that stuff. Tried force stopping the app. Im really frustrated. The app is good; but the glitches are really bad.
it is so hard to find an app stellar like this,it's so simple„ÄÅwonderful and easy to use. It literially can help you to focus and the design is sooo cute

Mostly purchased this app for the adorable bear. Flipping over the phone to start and pause the timer is a surprisingly nice way of controlling a pomodoro. The "settings" button in the bottom left corner fit in so well with the rest of the design that I thought it was just a little sun, hence it took me an embarassing amount of time to find it. 4 stars because I'd like a simple statistics page in the settings telling me how long I studied each day/week. If it had this function I'd rate it 5/5.
Does not work! Timer is constantly set at 25 mins and nothing can be changed. Tried reinstalling but nothing has changed. Poor!
This app so so cute- I am in love. It is really useful and has a simple interface that doesn't bombard you with unimportant functions.
A cute app that stops working after a couple of times... Too bad!

I wanted a simple pomodoro timer with no useless extra features, most definitely with no weird permission requests and with somewhat decent UI. Just bought this and it seems that it meets all of my needs and also with super cute design as an added bonus. Don't know what's with the other reviews but it seems to be working as intended with my Pixel 3a.

Does not seem to have the correct functionality for Android. Does not play white noise or have any settings you can change. Shame. Was recommended to me by a colleague, but she is using an iPhone. She gets white noise etc. Don't recommend for Android. Thankfully got refund. Will use Alexa to play white noise and give a timer instead.
Worked at first. After a couple of days the timer stopped working when the phone is flipped. I uninstalled and reinstalled, nothing fixed.
How do you start the timer? Nothing happens when I flip the phone over. Device is Mate10 Edit: Appers to be fixed now. Starts when the phone is flipped.

Good app. But they should update it for Android devices!

Nice little app that does the job it has been designed for... However, 
please at least give an option to remove the 'notch' version of the bear 
image for those of us with notchless phones. App shortcuts would be nice 
too (i.e. to start the timer)
This app is really helpful to me. I'm exercising to focus without phone...

Fine, charming app, with cute illustrations and a simple, well executed 
premise. However the illustrations are clearly designed for an iPhone 
(specifically X). There's a cut out for the notch on the top (which leaves 
ugly jagged lines), and the flip-the-phone symbol on the bottom right is an 
iPhone Too. The app works fine, however much of the charm is lost because 
of it's shaky presentation. As a result this app feels like a cheap port. I 
would still recommend the app to those interested, would have given it 5 
stars if more effort was put into the port.
